HEADWORD: Heartstring
<hw>Heart"string`</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt"str⟦icr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A nerve or tendon, supposed to brace and sustain the heart.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sobbing, as if a <qex>heartstring</qex> broke.</q>
<rj><qau>Moore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartstruck</ent>⟦br⟧
